  "text": "Pod security context validation in kubernetes/kubernetes spans multiple layers and locations. The primary validation mechanisms are:\n\n1. **Pod Security Admission Policy Checks** (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/):\n   - `check_runAsNonRoot.go`: Validates that containers run as non-root users. The CheckRunAsNonRoot function implements a restricted-level check that requires runAsNonRoot=true in policy version 1.0+. The runAsNonRoot_1_0 function validates both pod-level and container-level securityContext.runAsNonRoot fields.\n   - `check_privileged.go`: Validates that containers do not run in privileged mode. The CheckPrivileged function implements a baseline-level check that forbids privileged=true in 1.0+. The privileged_1_0 function checks securityContext.privileged field on containers.\n   - `check_capabilities_baseline.go`: Validates capabilities at the baseline level. CheckCapabilitiesBaseline restricts added capabilities to a default set (AUDIT_WRITE, CHOWN, DAC_OVERRIDE, FOWNER, FSETID, KILL, MKNOD, NET_BIND_SERVICE, SETFCAP, SETGID, SETPCAP, SETUID, SYS_CHROOT). The capabilitiesBaseline_1_0 function examines securityContext.capabilities.add field.\n   - `check_capabilities_restricted.go`: Implements restricted-level capabilities validation. CheckCapabilitiesRestricted ensures ALL capabilities are dropped and only NET_BIND_SERVICE can be added. Functions capabilitiesRestricted_1_22 and capabilitiesRestricted_1_25 validate securityContext.capabilities.drop and .add fields with Windows pod exemption in 1.25+.\n   - `check_seccompProfile_baseline.go`: Validates seccomp profiles at baseline level. CheckSeccompBaseline allows only RuntimeDefault and Localhost profiles. Functions seccompProfileBaseline_1_0 and seccompProfileBaseline_1_19 validate both legacy annotations (seccomp.security.alpha.kubernetes.io/*) and the securityContext.seccompProfile.type field. Helper functions validSeccomp and validSeccompAnnotationValue verify profile types.\n   - `check_seccompProfile_restricted.go`: Implements restricted-level seccomp validation. CheckSeccompProfileRestricted requires seccomp profiles to be explicitly set. Functions seccompProfileRestricted_1_19 and seccompProfileRestricted_1_25 enforce that all containers have valid seccomp profiles, with Windows pod exemption in 1.25+.\n\n2. **Core API Validation** (pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go):\n   - `ValidateSecurityContext`: Top-level function that validates container-level security context, checking privileged mode and capabilities constraints.\n   - `validatePodSpecSecurityContext`: Validates pod-level security context including checking for privileged restrictions and sysctls validation.\n   - `validateSeccompProfileField`: Validates the format and values of seccomp profile specifications.\n   - `validateSeccompProfileType`: Ensures seccomp profile type is one of the allowed values (RuntimeDefault, Localhost).\n   - `validateSeccompAnnotationsAndFieldsMatch`: Validates that seccomp settings specified in both annotations and fields are consistent.\n\n3. **Kubelet Runtime Implementation** (pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/):\n   - `security_context.go`: Contains `determineEffectiveSecurityContext` which determines the effective security context by merging pod and container-level settings, and `convertToRuntimeSecurityContext` which converts v1.SecurityContext to runtime API format, handling privileged, capabilities, and seccomp settings.\n   - `security_context_others.go`: Platform-specific security context implementation for Linux.\n\n4. **Security Context Accessors** (pkg/securitycontext/):\n   - `accessors.go`: Defines `PodSecurityContextAccessor` interface and related mutators for accessing and modifying security context fields including RunAsNonRoot, SeccompProfile, and other settings.\n   - `util.go`: Provides utility functions for security context operations.\n\nThese components work together to validate pod security context fields at multiple levels: admission control (pod-security-admission policy), API validation (core validation), and runtime enforcement (kubelet), ensuring comprehensive enforcement of security context constraints throughout the pod lifecycle."
